Utterances.UttText: S: Ms Cage is a 56 year old female with a history of HTN who presents for chest pain.

Phrases.PhraseText: a 56 year old female with a history of HTN

Utterances.UttText: She had an episode 3 days ago related to exertion where she felt a pressure like pain in her mid chest whithout radiation.

Phrases.PhraseText: in her mid chest whithout radiation.

Utterances.UttText: This resolved in 5-10 mintues with rest, there was no relation to eating, and the pain was not related to breathing or coughing.
She has had pain similar to this 2-3 times over the last 4 months without any SOB.

Phrases.PhraseText: over the last 4 months without any SOB.

Utterances.UttText: She has also had some pains in her lower chest that are related to eating big meals.

Phrases.PhraseText: some pains in her lower chest

Utterances.UttText: There is no associated nausea or vomiting with the most recent CP that she is worried about.

Phrases.PhraseText: vomiting with the most recent CP

Utterances.UttText: She denies palpitations, CP/SOB at rest/leg swelling.
She did not notice any other modifying factors or associated symptoms.
She is worried if she might have had a heart attack.

PMhx: HTN Meds: Chlorthalidone 25mg; lisinopril 10mg FamHx: dad died at 40 from MI, CAD, CABG - mom died at 60 from PE, DM2, HTN -MGM had breast CA Social: 30pack year active smoker, 2-3 glasses wine on weekedn, no illicit drug use  O: Temp 98 P 85 R 14 BP 150/92  PE HEENT: EOM intact, thyroid normal Cardiac: Normal rate/rhythm, no m/r/g, normal s1,s2 no peripheral edema, no chest tenderness, +2 radial, DP,PT,carotid pulses b/l Resp: normal breath sounds b/l Abd: no tenderness, normal b/s, non dist  A Ms Cage is a 56 year old female with a history of HTN presenting for episodic CP related to exertion.

Phrases.PhraseText: Temp 98 P 85 R 14 BP 150/92  PE HEENT
a 56 year old female with a history of HTN presenting

Utterances.UttText: She is hypertensive in office today and her physical exam is normal  Plan: EKG, CBC, BMP, troponin today in office, will send to ER if EKG is abnormal.
